<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued January 02 at 5:20AM CST until January 02 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST TODAY...
* WHAT...A mix of light freezing rain, sleet, and snow. Trace ice
accumulations may result in a light glaze, especially on
elevated surfaces. Only trace accumulations of snow are
expected.
* WHERE...Portions of north central and northwest Louisiana,
south central and southwest Arkansas and east and northeast
Texas.
* WHEN...Until noon CST today.
* IMPACTS...Very slippery sidewalks, roads and bridges are
possible, but isolated slick spots may occur.</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling. Prepare for possible
power outages.
The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.</instruction>
